<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="149" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,499,260,287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">Biology and distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Roza &amp; Mermudes, 2019" authorityName="Roza &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2019" box="[507,725,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="queirozi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[507,725,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">Hylotribus queirozi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[733,823,261,287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[733,823,261,287]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
occurs during the Southern Hemisphere summer (December). It inhabits high elevation areas of PARNASO, in 
<collectingRegion box="[819,1050,297,323]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">Rio de Janeiro State</collectingRegion>
, at 
<quantity box="[1090,1187,297,323]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.941" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" unit="m" value="1941.0">1,941 m</quantity>
. It occurs in the highmontane forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="149" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,153,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,369,395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Roza &amp; Mermudes, 2019" authorityName="Roza &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,539,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="queirozi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,539,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">Hylotribus queirozi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[546,635,369,395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[546,635,369,395]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[650,776,368,395]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–15" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1966,1991]" captionTargetBox="[259,1342,253,1923]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[212,1376,237,1941]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 11–15. Hylotribus queirozi sp. nov., holotype male from Brasil, Teresópolis-RJ. 11. Habitus, dorsal; 12. Habitus, lateral; 13. Head and rostrum, frontal; 14. Pronotum; 15. Prothorax, lateral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3573510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3573510/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">Figs 11–15</figureCitation>
) differs from the other species by the diagnostic characters cited above, but mainly by having the pronotum with a longitudinal narrow anteriorly oriented pale yellow stripe extending from the median tubercle and divided past the anterobasal carinae forming an inverted V-shaped pattern reaching the posterior margin of the pronotum. This character is otherwise present only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Roza &amp; Mermudes, 2019" authorityName="Roza &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2019" box="[1188,1336,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humeralis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1188,1336,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">H. humeralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1345,1436,477,503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1345,1436,477,503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
However, the elytral humeri of 
<taxonomicName authority="Roza &amp; Mermudes, 2019" authorityName="Roza &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2019" box="[516,665,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humeralis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[516,665,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">H. humeralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[674,767,513,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[674,767,513,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have lateral tufted pale yellow scales, these lacking in 
<taxonomicName authority="Roza &amp; Mermudes, 2019" authorityName="Roza &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="queirozi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">H. queirozi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[249,338,549,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[249,338,549,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Queiroz &amp; Mermudes, 2014" authorityName="Queiroz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2014" box="[559,1038,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
<emphasis box="[559,713,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">H. plaumanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Queiroz, F. A. &amp; Mermudes, J. R. M." box="[720,1038,549,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" pagination="242 - 258" refId="ref11373" refString="Queiroz, F. A. &amp; Mermudes, J. R. M. (2014) Six new species of Hylotribus Jekel, 1860 (Coleoptera, Anthribidae, Anthribinae, Discotenini) from Brazil. Zootaxa, 3814 (2), 242 - 258. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3814.2.5" type="journal article" year="2014">Queiroz &amp; Mermudes, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but has the basal gibbosity slightly larger than the ante-apical tubercles (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Queiroz &amp; Mermudes" authorityYear="2014" box="[567,721,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Anthribidae" genus="Hylotribus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="149" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
<emphasis box="[567,721,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="149">H. plaumanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the ante-apical tubercles larger than the basal gibbosity).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
